IBADAN – Oyo State Government on Tuesday, suspended a Secondary school student in the state, Ojo Roqeeb, over assault of a National Youth Corps Service (NYSC) member. The Commissioner for Education, Science and Technology, Barrister Rahman Abiodun Abdu-Raheem, who frowned at a reported case of a SSS 2 student of Anglican Commercial Secondary School, Orita-Mefa Ibadan, Ojo Roqeeb, who slapped a corp member, ordered an immediate one-month suspension for the student. The Commissioner, who visited the school also ordered that a letter of suspension be given to his parents, saying the student, on return, will have to apologize to the corp member and sign an undertaking. Woman Kidnaps Five Children In Rivers AMAC Chairman-Elect Appeals To Buhari To Assent Amendment… While addressing the students, the Commissioner charged them to be of good behaviour, reiterating that the Oyo State government will not condone any act of indiscipline. He sternly warned that any student caught, acting in an uncivilized manner, will henceforth be dismissed from schools in Oyo State. Barrister Abdu-Raheem also charged teachers to be more dedicated and punctual at work.